main event: Three witnesses observed a pulsating saucer-shaped object in the sky over Frankfort, Kentucky on January 17-18, 1967.
interesting points: The object was described as yellow-green, 8-10 feet in diameter, and visible for 1.3 hours., The object displayed movements up and down, side to side, with speeds estimated between 6-20 mph., The colors of the object included red, yellow, and green, and it pulsated on and off., Observers believed the object was not an aircraft and had witnessed similar phenomena in the days prior., There was a power failure in the area a day before the sighting, suggesting a possible correlation.
witness description: Civilian witnesses with some experience in observing lights on night-flying aircraft.
